# Memory Discipline Rules

1. Treat `.cursor/memories/roadmap.md` as the single progress tracker.
2. Keep memory files lean; remove stale product references during pivot work.
3. Treat `.cursor/memories/architecture.md` as the latest agreed system shape.
4. Treat `.cursor/memories/architecture-decisions.md` as rationale only.
5. Keep `Session Briefing` current and concise in roadmap.
6. Put unresolved reproducible blockers only in `.cursor/memories/debuglog.md`.
7. Put reusable lessons only in `.cursor/memories/memo.md`.
8. Treat `.cursor/memories/product-blueprint.md` as canonical product intent.
9. Avoid duplication; each fact should have one home.
